@Node Main "Reg_English.guide"



@{b}Registering Vapor Software@{ub}
**************************

Thank you for supporting Amiga Software Development! By registering the
Software you use, you ensure further development of high quality Amiga
applications!


 @{" How To Use " Link "How To Use"}          How to use the registration utility
 @{" Registration Sites " Link "Registration Sites"}  Information on registration sites
 @{" Manually " Link "Manually"}            Registering without the registration utility
 @{" Problems " Link "Problems"}            If you have any problems...
 @{" Support " Link "Support"}             How to get support and updates

- Other stuff: -

 @{" License " Link "License"}             General Software License
 @{" Index " Link "Index"}               Index of this Document

The information presented in this document is valid as of @{i}February,
23th 1997@{ui}. Please check out the @{"WWW Support Site" Link "Support"} for latest information.


@EndNode

@Node "How To Use" "Reg_English.guide/How To Use"
@Next "Registration Sites"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

How To Use
**********

The registration utility provides an easy, GUI driven means to gather
all necessary information required for registration.  It also
calculates resulting fees and discounts, and shows all options
available. You can print the resulting registration form or directly
mail it via Internet mail if you have an Internet connection.

After starting the program, you will be shown the main window.
Depending on your screen size, the window contents may be larger than
the visible size of your screen. Use the window's scrollbars to move
the contents just as you do with Workbench windows.

Fill in the necessary personal information and select the registration
site, method of payment and products you want to register.

The order list will immediately calculate the fee based on your
selection of products and the costs per registration site.

You can quit the registration program at any time. All the information
you have filled in will be saved in the file @{b}S:Vapor.Reginfo@{ub} and is
automatically reloaded when you start the registration program the next
time.

When you have finished filling out the fields, you have four options on
how to proceed with the finally generated registration form.

   - The button @{b}Save form to file@{ub} allows you to save the resulting
     registration form to a disk file. You can inspect the file with a
     text viewer like @{b}More@{ub} or include it into your favorite EMail
     package to mail the form.

   - The button @{b}Print form@{ub} prints the resulting form on your printer.

   - Pressing @{b}Mail form via net@{ub} attempts to automatically mail the
     resulting form via Internet. In order for this to work, you must
     have a working Internet connection and a TCP/IP stack loaded. You
     are informed of the success or failure of this operation.

   - With pressing @{b}View form@{ub}, a text window opens presenting  the
     resulting registration form. You are encouraged to check out the
     form before printing or mailing it.


@EndNode

@Node "Registration Sites" "Reg_English.guide/Registration Sites"
@Next "Manually"
@Prev "How To Use"
@Toc "Main"

Registration Sites
******************

As of the time of writing, there were 6 registration sites available.

      @{"Germany" Link "Germany"}         reg-de@vapor.com  @{b}Cash, EC, PC, BT, PM@{ub}
      @{"UK" Link "UK"}              reg-uk@vapor.com  @{b}Cash, EC, PC, CC, PM, CR@{ub}
      @{"Sweden" Link "Sweden"}          reg-se@vapor.com  @{b}Cash, BT, PM@{ub}
      @{"France" Link "France"}          reg-fr@vapor.com  @{b}Cash, EC, PC, CC, BT, PM@{ub}
      @{"USA" Link "USA"}             reg-us@vapor.com  @{b}Cash, PC, CC, PM, FV@{ub}
      @{"Canada" Link "Canada"}          reg-ca@vapor.com  @{b}Cash, PC, CC, PM@{ub}
      @{"Australia" Link "Australia"}       reg-au@vapor.com  @{b}Cash, PC, CC, PM@{ub}

The second column designates the email address of the registration
site. If you have any questions regarding registration, feel free to
write to this address.

The third column specifies which methods of payment are accepted by the
specific registration site:

@{b}Cash@{ub}
     Plain, good old @{i}Cash@{ui} included with the registration letter.  This
     is not encouraged since such letters tend to "get lost" in some
     countries esspecially if coins are included.

@{b}EC@{ub}
     @{i}Eurocheque@{ui}. Eurocheques are guaranteed by the issueing bank and
     therefore are "good by definition", not imposing any clearance
     delay on registration processing.

@{b}PC@{ub}
@{b}CC@{ub}
     @{i}Personal Cheque@{ui} and @{i}Cashiers Cheque@{ui}. This will delay the process
     of the registration until the cheque is sucessfully cleared.
     Please make the cheque payable to the owner of the specific
     registration site.

@{b}BT@{ub}
     @{i}Bank transaction@{ui}. Generally only available in the same country as
     the registration site is located in. Please put a clear reference
     to your registration mail onto the transaction sheet, so that
     payment and registration can be linked.

@{b}PM@{ub}
     @{i}Postal money order@{ui}. Sometimes also called @{i}International Money
     Order@{ui}. Please put a clear reference to your registration mail
     onto the transaction sheet, so that payment and registration can
     be linked.

@{b}FV@{ub}
     @{i}First Virtual Electronic Transaction@{ui}. A means of payment through
     pure electronic channels. See `http://www.fv.com/' for more
     information about First Virtual.

@{b}CR@{ub}
     @{i}Credit Card@{ui}. Directly bill your credit card.


@EndNode

