@Node "Manually" "Reg_English.guide/Manually"
@Next "Problems"
@Prev "Registration Sites"
@Toc "Main"

Registering Manually
********************

If you, for some reason, don't want to use the registration program,
you can of course register manually. Information about registration
sites, prices and methods of payment can be found in the section
@{"Registration Sites" Link "Registration Sites"}.

Please make sure you include all the necessary information in the
letter or email you send, especially your address and what you want to
register!

All sites grant a @{i}discount@{ui} for multi-unit registrations.  This
discount is 5% for 2 to 4 units and 10% at 5 or more units. Make sure
you subtract this discount before you calculate the final registration
fee!


@EndNode

@Node "Problems" "Reg_English.guide/Problems"
@Next "Support"
@Prev "Manually"
@Toc "Main"

Problems
********

Trouble with the registration utility
=====================================

If you have any trouble starting or using the registration utility,
please write a bug report to @{b}bugs@vapor.com@{ub}.  Please include a
extensive problem description and an overview of your system
configuration.

@{i}Bug reports which help to track down a formerly not known bug in the
registration utility will be rewarded a 50% discount on a single
registration of your choice!@{ui}

You can also register manually in such a case; see the section @{"Manually" Link "Manually"}
on how to do that.

Trouble with the registration process
=====================================

Well, what if you have sent the money and registration and you don't
get your key files or disks?

Of course, we hope that this never happens. However, experience tells
us that problems with email do occur, and the following instructions
are @{i}Just in case@{ui}.  Please understand that none of the registration
sites will just cash in your money and not send anything back just for
being evil, as no one would actually benefit from that.

First, allow about a 4 week processing delay before you start to worry
about your registration, to cover snail mail delay, cheque clearance
and related stuff.

Write a email to the specific registration site to find out what is
happening. If you don't get a reply to such an inquiry, something is
probably broken.

Most likely, something is wrong with your email link in such a case.
Write a test message to @{b}bounceme@vapor.com@{ub}, which should trigger a
automatical informational message that your message has arrived at
vapor.com's mail system. If this works, please write to
@{b}reg-trouble@vapor.com@{ub} specifying what's wrong.

If you however @{i}don't@{ui} get a response from @{b}bounceme@vapor.com@{ub}, something
is definitvly broken with your mail account.  In that case, your
registration email probably never arrived, or the key file sent to you
was lost on it's way.  Try a different mail account, if you have one,
or resort to traditional snail mail then.


@EndNode

@Node "Support" "Reg_English.guide/Support"
@Next "License"
@Prev "Problems"
@Toc "Main"

Support
*******

There are several means of getting support and updates for Vapor
products.

Internet
========

   @{b}*@{ub} WWW (World Wide Web)

     The URL for the WWW support pages is @{b}http://www.vapor.com/support/@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub} FTP (File Transfer Protocol)

     Access to files is available from the server @{b}ftp.vapor.com@{ub} in
     directory @{b}/support@{ub}.

These two sites may be partially mirrored on other sites.  Availability
of mirrors will be announced on the main sites.

E-Mail
======

Vapor runs a number of @{i}mailing lists@{ui} which provide support for the
various products. To learn how to access these lists, write a mail to
@{b}listserv@vapor.com@{ub} and put the following two lines in the mail body:

        HELP
        LONGINDEX

You will in return receive a mail giving instructions on how to use the
listserver, and an index of currently available mailing lists.

You can access the listserver with internet mail and every online
service which provides an gateway to internet mail, for example
Compuserve or AOL.

In order to access files via email, you can use the @{i}file server@{ui}. Write
a mail to @{b}fileserv@vapor.com@{ub} containing the lines

     	HELP
     	LIST

to receive instructions and a list of available files.

Modem
=====

We are currently in the process of setting up a BBS which provides
direct access to files via Modem and ISDN service. This service will be
announced as soon as it is available.

Many Amiga supporting BBSes will provide access to @{i}AmiNet@{ui} files, and
since major updates and releases of Vapor products will always be
uploaded to AmiNet, you are able to download these files there.


@EndNode

